(457, 1, '2012-06-08 21:32:23', '2012-06-08 21:32:23', 'You cannot despise the box in which the gift comes in, if you intend to love the gift. This means on a level of conscious observation one should not love the internal gift a person brings into your life through their personality and character, but on the contrary behave in a way that leaves you to question if you despise the shell the gift came in. Perception is the challenge for the one who intends to perceive, but a gift from within is to be cherished and loved. Any emotion that would have one side tracked into a dual perception of what a internal gift is, should be observed and concluded as the arrival of the false self or the ego. In the valley of death every internal gift is a blessings from the heavens to assist in ones self development in a evolutionary process. Spiritual growth has been a priority for myself during my life journey, which has seemed like forever and a day, but through my journey in the pursuit of wisdom and understanding I have become conscious of the chaos brewing deep within. I would want nothing more then to release it into the cosmos, destroy and rebuild and <em>Create Society. </em>In the mean time, there is much more to learn about the advancement of not only my gift, but the gift that the Creator has placed in each and everyone of us to be expressed creatively during our spiritual experience here and now. I know our gifts and passions are immeasurable in all aspects, for a god in the perfect pursuit of perfection, evolution is the only option. Tho I am also guilty of materialism , every state of mind was created as a shell to grow out of. I intend to keep growing until I grow out of the current state of being.\r\n\r\n- Create Society', 'Intelligence Is A Blessing And A Curse.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'intelligence-is-a-blessing-and-a-curse', '', '', '2012-06-09 02:11:42', '2012-06-09 02:11:42', '', 0, 'http://creationofsociety.com/wp/?p=457', 0, 'post', '', 1),
