(508, 1, '2012-07-08 13:38:04', '2012-07-08 20:38:04', '[nggallery id=20]\r\n\r\nWhat seemed like another day in North Oakland quickly turned into a surreal moment when I saw Fred''s God dad Standing on his truck picking fruits from the plum tree on the corner. Ricky Henderson who is also an Oakland Native, became famous in the baseball world for his elite inner city baseball attitude as well as his hard knock work ethic. Growing up playing baseball at Greenmans field in Oakland''s inner city Rickey Henderson''s style of play was something that all the kids of our generation imitated. Whether it was his batting style at home plate or his very untraditional head first, full stretch, superman style slides into second base when he stole from first base. Which he did over fourteen hundred times, which reigns supreme over any player who wishes to hold that title in Major League Baseball. Nicknamed the '' Man of Steal'' because of his dependability over his two decade stint with Major League Baseball Mr. Henderson was not only respected for his speed on the bases but is also regarded as one of baseballs greatest lead off hitters of all time, holding the record for most home runs as a lead off hitter. Rickey Henderson was one of those Athletes that young black baseball players attached themselves too, not only in Oakland but the nation as well, if you planned on being one of the greatest you needed to pay attention to how Rickey was doing it, because he was defiantly one of the greatest to play the game. One thing that I believe is over looked about Mr. Henderson is his business ethics, he wasn''t just one of those guys who made a lot of money and didn''t know what to do with it. Mr. Henderson was smart about his investments, participating in real estate and self sustainable agriculture he has set a blueprint for young black men trying to navigate through america''s corporate society. Since Rickey Henderson''s Domination of the MLB there has been a sustainable drop in american black men in baseball, which has consequently locked black men out of the professional network that comes along with the participation of americas favorite pass time. This fact pays homage to the concept of the glass ceiling in the american society being that only a elected few will rise to professional stardom and be granted access to a professional world that the masses could only dream of. Rickey Henderson was one of those guys elected to represent Oakland on a global scale, and he did just that.\r\n\r\n- Create Society\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Chilling With A Local Legend, Ricky Henderson!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chilling-with-a-local-legend-ricky-henderson', '', '', '2012-07-08 21:20:09', '2012-07-09 04:20:09', '', 0, 'http://creationofsociety.com/?p=508', 0, 'post', '', 0),
