(521, 1, '2012-07-08 21:50:16', '2012-07-09 04:50:16', '<a href="http://creationofsociety.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/217267_106668782752100_106314189454226_66626_7219777_n.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-523" title="Create Society" src="http://creationofsociety.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/217267_106668782752100_106314189454226_66626_7219777_n-300x199.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="199" /></a>\r\n\r\nIt’s fact by now that the recent college grads of the Gen Y era are finding job success in areas outside the traditional manner. Though the economy still plays a vital role in sustaining a high unemployment percentage, there are still plenty of opportunities out there, especially for ambitious entrepreneurs. What do you think of when you hear the word entrepreneur? What do you imagine an entrepreneur’s job to be like? We all know that being an entrepreneur means taking a risk to become successful in a business venture. That’s a given. However, to what extent would you measure a successful entrepreneur? What defines success? The general consensus may be wealth, but this article discusses a rather different approach to the concept. Christen Brown, Co Creator of <a href="http://creationofsociety.com/"><em>Creation Of Society Clothing and Apparel</em></a>, embodies the ideology of a socially conscious entrepreneur. His mentality and awareness of social issues and universal connection has manifested into a company that is gaining momentum among supporters.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://creationofsociety.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/cos-team.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-527" title="cos-team" src="http://creationofsociety.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/cos-team.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="199" /></a>\r\n\r\nAlong with the brilliant works co creator and head designer Udoka Uwakwe, C.O.S. delivers a powerful message behind their shirts. With such messages as, “Dream Big or Wake Up” and “Focused on Me,” C.O.S. is promoting a unique brand message that directly connects with customers. “The brand has a multidimensional meaning,” said Brown. “We create this wearable art that perpetuates a product of our environment which by definition is Creation Of Society. In order to create or be creative, one must be conscious of self.” The C.O.S. mission reflects their global perspectives and allows the team to connect with supporters by not only sharing knowledge, but also by inspiring the youth to be creative and follow their passions. In essence, to influence the creation of a positive society for all. Pretty powerful meaning behind a clothing brand. Yet, it is this kind of ambition as a young entrepreneur that defines success. C.O.S. is able to connect with supporters in ways many big corporations continue to struggle with. If you had the ability to influence someone to wear a statement that represents social change, inspiration and conscious awareness, wouldn’t you say that defines success?\r\n\r\nFor more inspiring untold stories of young entrepreneurs in OUR Generation Y, check out &amp; subscribe to OUR<a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/jmw247?feature=mhee"><em>YouTube!!</em></a>', 'Creating Society For Our Generation ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'creating-society-for-our-generation-y', '', '', '2012-07-09 00:56:15', '2012-07-09 07:56:15', '', 0, 'http://creationofsociety.com/?p=521', 0, 'post', '', 0),
